(42, 21, 22, 41, 13, 19, 20, 'these be the days of vengeance', 'Days of Affliction and Vengeance', 'Both passages emphasize a period of intense suffering and divine action. Luke refers to ''the days of vengeance,'' while Mark describes ''affliction'' and the shortening of those days for the elect.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
